If youâ€™re getting an error that says â€œNo bean found for JavaMailSenderâ€, it usually means that Spring Boot is not automatically configuring the mail sender. Letâ€™s troubleshoot and fix it step by step.

â¸»

âœ… 1ï¸âƒ£ Ensure Dependencies are Correct

Your build.gradle file should have:

dependencies {
    implementation 'org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-mail'
    implementation 'org.eclipse.angus:jakarta.mail:1.6.7'
}

Run:

./gradlew build --refresh-dependencies

to ensure everything is installed properly.

â¸»

âœ… 2ï¸âƒ£ Check Your application.properties or application.yml

Make sure you have the correct SMTP configurations:

ğŸ”¹ application.properties

